Missions.Title: Ghost Shift
Missions.Description: The fab agreed to stop production over night to make investigations possible. The few workers remain, making sure production can continue the next day.

Objectives.Description: A copy of Mutant Zombie Laser Ninja from Hell and Outer Space.

Missions.Title: Warehouse B
Missions.Description: It turns out somebody used fake components with "alternative" integrated circuits to create their own parts during an extra shift. Those ICs came from warehouse B. As you arrive there, the building is apparently taken by some goons...

Missions.Title: Distraction
Missions.Description:
You get a warning from military command: Those are fanatic terrorists with a misguided sympathy for synthetic life. Their favorite strategy is creating distractions.
Unfortunately you hear shots just the minute you read that message. You've got no choice but to go for it.

Objectives.Description: Activate emergency shelter for the civilians.

Missions.Title: Dream Sequence
Missions.Description: Before you can enter a safehouse yourself, you slip and hit your head. It gets dark... Fortunately, you are a lucid dreamer.

Missions.Title: Ruins
Missions.Description: As you wake up you realize the whole district has been destroyed. Seems like the fanatics didn't need a distraction after all. You need to get out of here, fast.

Objectives.Description: This isn't the time to create paper planes!

Missions.Title: Resistance
Missions.Description: Looks like the fanatics finally managed to get their hands on military grade robots. Some of them even got some upgrade on themselves. You can't tell if they are actually controlled by AI, but they sure are dangerous lunatics...

Objectives.Description: Get to the ogre army squad leader.

Missions.Title: Sweep
Missions.Description: The ogre squad leader tells you that the terrorists have indeed implanted themselves with microchips that allow them to be controlled by an AI. Before you can do anything about it you need to clear the perimeter, because some of the now controlled fanatics seem to have made it into the base.

Missions.Title: Valley
Missions.Description: None of the soldiers survived the attack. At least you learned the location of the central AI node.

Missions.Title: The Core
Missions.Description: Now that you are in the facility that contains the AI cluster you have to destroy all systems.

Missions.Title: Escape
Missions.Description: Destroying all these devices started a fire. The only way out is through the basement, but you notice that there are still killbots between you and the exit. The AI must have sent a signal to self-destruct on sight...
